Guess which Pagani car is Horacio's favourite. The answer's neither Zonda nor Huayra - but, MARA!
He designed and crafted MARA (whose name comes from his parent's initials) when he was 11-12, and still, it is his favourite car. 

Today is the day - the Motor Valley Fest has officially started and will last until Sunday. Come to see live MARA and other Horacio's childhood projects right beside some wonderful Pagani Hypercars. 

#horaciopaganimuseo #pagani #MotorValley @motorvalleyofficial #modena

The four exhausts of Zonda have certainly become an icon of Pagani Automobili over time. Still, you won't believe where this concept comes from!

Come over and say hi, we'll be waiting for you in Piazza Grande, Modena. 

#Pagani #Zonda #mvf #mvf21 #motorvalleyfest #modena

Will it do the same to you? Come to find it out at the Motor Valley Fest!

Have you ever wondered how the four exhausts were born? Or even what inspired the shape of Huayra's side mirror? Stay tuned to find it out!

node.text:
Dedicated to someone exceptional.

Beyond its stunning design and highly impressive technical stats, the Huayra BC is also one of the most beloved Pagani Hypercars because of its name and the story of friendship behind it. 

BC stands for Benny Caiola, who made history as the first customer to buy a Pagani car. He was impressed by the passion and technology that went into the cars Horacio was designing right from the outset, and it is to him that the Huayra BC is dedicated.

Conceived primarily as a road-going car, the Huayra BC was inspired by its “track-focused” predecessors - the Pagani Zonda R and the Zonda Cinque. Developed as a natural evolution of the Coupé, the car is pure raw power packaged into a 1218-kg high-performance automobile.

#Pagani #Huayra #HuayraBC #Monterey2021 #MontereyCarWeek

The C9 project, better known as Pagani Huayra, turns 10 this year! A fantastic path that quickly got off on the right foot - in 2012, 3 times the most prestigious automotive magazines awarded it "Car of the Year". 

And yet, this outstanding and immediate achievement didn't prevent Horacio Pagani and his team from consistently improving this marvel in all areas. This is one of the cornerstones of Pagani Automobili: when you compete against yourselves only, all you can do is doing better. 

In the next weeks, right before Monterey Car Week, during which we'll be celebrating the Pagani Huayra, we'll take an interesting journey through its evolution, taking a look at each variant... and much more! 
You ready?
